This paper focuses on the optimization of power consumption in a wireless communication system, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of multiple front ends and non-contiguous spectrum access also suggests a potential fit for the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the use of Multi-Channel Multi-Radio (MC-MR) and Non-Contiguous Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing (NC-OFDM) technologies suggests a potential fit for the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories, respectively.
